PROVENANCE

  Pi4J project
    https://pi4j.com
    https://github.com/Pi4J
    Pi4J is a Java I/O library for Raspberry Pi maintained by the Pi4J project.

  pi4j-components (upstream of this fork)
    Originally extracted from the Pi4J example applications
    (https://github.com/Pi4J/pi4j-example-components, related repos under
    the Pi4J GitHub organisation). Provides reusable component wrappers —
    LEDs, buttons, joysticks, servos, ADCs, LCD displays, GPS, etc. —
    around the core pi4j-core API.

  Repackaged for the ParadigmShift ecosystem
    pt.paradigmshift.iot:pi4j-components
    https://www.paradigmshift.pt
    Maven coordinates and build / release plumbing changed; package paths
    (com.pi4j.catalog.*) are unchanged so existing consumers can switch by
    editing their pom.xml only. The unused picocli dependency and its
    annotation processor, plus the maven-dependency-plugin distribution
    bundling, were removed because this artifact is published as a library
    and not a runnable application.

